# Hostel Management System – Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A full-stack Hostel Management System (35% scope) with a **navy/teal** themed UI matching your reference image, 11 HTML pages, shared header/footer/nav, JS validation, and a Node.js + MySQL REST API.

---

## Project Structure

```
new project/
├── frontend/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css          ← Global styles (navy #1a2b4a + teal #00b4d8)
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── common.js          ← Header/footer builder, session, validation helpers
│   └── pages/
│       ├── register.html      ← Student registration + full validation
│       ├── login.html         ← Login with demo credentials
│       ├── profile.html       ← View / update student profile
│       ├── admin-users.html   ← Admin: manage users, activate/deactivate
│       ├── rooms.html         ← Real-time room availability (grid & list view)
│       ├── room-allocate.html ← Admin: allocate rooms to students
│       ├── fee-structure.html ← Admin: add/edit/delete fee types
│       ├── fee-payment.html   ← Record payments + history + CSV export
│       ├── visitor-register.html ← Visitor registration + policy sidebar
│       ├── visitor-history.html  ← Visitor log: approve/reject/filter
│       └── about.html         ← About Us page with team, facilities, contact
│
└── backend/
    ├── server.js              ← Express entry point (port 5000)
    ├── db.js                  ← MySQL2 connection pool
    ├── .env                   ← DB credentials + JWT secret
    ├── schema.sql             ← All 6 tables + seed data
    ├── middleware/
    │   └── auth.js            ← JWT authenticate + requireAdmin guards
    └── routes/
        ├── auth.js            ← POST /api/auth/register, /login
        ├── users.js           ← GET/PUT/PATCH/DELETE /api/users
        ├── rooms.js           ← GET/POST /api/rooms, /allocate
        ├── fees.js            ← GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/fees/structure, /payment
        └── visitors.js        ← GET/POST/PATCH /api/visitors
```

