## 🚀 How to Run

### 1 – Open frontend directly (no backend needed)
All pages work in demo mode with sample data:
```
Open: frontend/pages/login.html  in your browser
```

### 2 – Set up MySQL database
```sql
-- In MySQL Workbench / phpMyAdmin / terminal:
SOURCE d:/SLIIT/2nd year/2nd sem/ITP/new project/backend/schema.sql;
```

### 3 – Configure [.env](file:///d:/SLIIT/2nd%20year/2nd%20sem/ITP/new%20project/backend/.env)
```
d:/SLIIT/2nd year/2nd sem/ITP/new project/backend/.env
```
Edit `DB_PASSWORD=` if your MySQL has a password.

### 4 – Start the backend server
```powershell
cd "d:\SLIIT\2nd year\2nd sem\ITP\new project\backend"
npm run dev        # uses nodemon (auto-restart)
# OR
npm start          # plain node
```

Server starts at: **http://localhost:5000**
Frontend served at: **http://localhost:5000/pages/login.html**

### 5 – API Endpoints Summary

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | Register new user |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Login → returns JWT |
| GET | `/api/users` | All users (admin) |
| PATCH | `/api/users/:id/status` | Activate/deactivate |
| GET | `/api/rooms` | All rooms with status |
| POST | `/api/rooms/allocate` | Allocate room |
| GET | `/api/fees/structure` | Fee structures |
| POST | `/api/fees/payment` | Record payment |
| GET | `/api/visitors` | Visitor history |
| POST | `/api/visitors` | Register visitor |
| PATCH | `/api/visitors/:id/status` | Approve/reject |

---

## Validation Rules Enforced

- **Name** – min 3 characters
- **Email** – regex pattern `user@domain.ext`
- **NIC** – `9 digits + V/X` OR `12 digits`
- **Phone** – exactly 10 digits
- **Password** – min 8 chars, strength indicator shown
- **Confirm Password** – must match
- **Date fields** – visit date must be today or future; end date after start date
- **Amount fields** – must be positive numbers
- **Number of visitors** – 1 to 5 only

All validations fire **live on input/blur** and again on submit.
